9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
10 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 509 of Title 19, unless there is
12 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Volunteer
14 County Emergency Response Corps Act”.
15 B. 1. The county sheriff, county commissioners, and emergency
16 management personnel of each county of this state shall work in
17 conjunction to establish a system to engage county residents to
18 volunteer their time, expertise, or resources during an emergency.
19 2. Prioritization for selection in the Volunteer County
20 Emergency Response Corps shall be based on, but not limited to, the
21 following:
22 a. construction services to clear debris,
23 b. landscaping services to clear downed trees,
24
